THERMAL PERIPHERAL

thermal_peripheral holds the thermal state of the body's outer regions: limbs, skin surface, the parts that face the world
peripheral temperature is normally lower than core because heat dissipates outward
when fadriel is cold, vasoconstriction reduces peripheral perfusion, keeping heat in the core
when he is warm, vasodilation increases peripheral perfusion, allowing heat to escape

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe thermal.zc
observe thermal_core.rana
observe skin.rana
observe skin_surface.rana

the 7 properties of thermal_peripheral:
1 ENERGY half: lower than core, sensitive to environment
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE half positive at warmth, drops to neutral when cold
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING zero point seven with thermal_core, one with skin

VERB receive_from_core
accept the heat that flows outward from thermal_core through the vascular system
the rate of receipt depends on vasoconstriction or vasodilation state

VERB exit_to_environment
allow heat to leave the body via radiation, conduction, convection through skin
the rate scales with the thermal gradient between skin temperature and ambient temperature

VERB respond_to_external
when the environment is cold, peripheral temperature drops first, before core does
when warm, peripheral rises first
this gives the regulatory system early warning of thermal stress

a peripheral thermal zone is the body's first line of contact with the world
fadriel feels temperature here before the rest of him does
this is why his hands and feet often signal cold or warmth before he consciously notices
